---

### ğŸ’» **Step 2: Create a Virtual Machine**

**Navigation:**
**Home â†’ Create a resource â†’ Compute â†’ Virtual Machine â†’ Create**

Then fill the **Basics tab** as follows ğŸ‘‡

| Setting                         | Value                                   |
| ------------------------------- | --------------------------------------- |
| **Subscription**                | Choose your available subscription      |
| **Resource Group**              | **Create new â†’ Name it `IntroAzureRG`** |
| **Virtual Machine Name**        | `my-VM`                                 |
| **Region**                      | Leave default                           |
| **Availability Options / Zone** | Leave default                           |
| **Security Type**               | Default                                 |
| **Image**                       | Default (Windows/Linux OS image)        |
| **VM Architecture**             | Default                                 |
| **Azure Spot Discount**         | Leave unchecked                         |
| **Size**                        | Default                                 |
| **Authentication Type**         | Password                                |
| **Username**                    | `azureuser`                             |
| **Password**                    | Create a secure password                |
| **Public Inbound Ports**        | None                                    |
| **Review + Create**             | Click **Create**                        |

> ğŸ’¡ **Tip:**
> If youâ€™re using a **Microsoft Learn Sandbox**, this is **free** and no real billing occurs.

