## ğŸ“¦ **3. Verify Resources Created**

**Navigation:**
**Home â†’ Resource Groups â†’ IntroAzureRG**

Here youâ€™ll see **multiple items** â€” not just the VM.

| Resource Type          | Example Name   | Description                          |
| ---------------------- | -------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| Virtual Machine        | `my-VM`        | The compute resource you created     |
| Network Interface      | `my-VM-nic`    | Connects the VM to a virtual network |
| Public IP              | `my-VM-ip`     | Provides external access             |
| Network Security Group | `my-VM-nsg`    | Controls inbound/outbound traffic    |
| Disk                   | `my-VM_disk1`  | OS disk attached to the VM           |
| Virtual Network        | `my-VM-vnet`   | Network environment for your VM      |
| Subnet                 | `my-VM-subnet` | Logical segment within the VNet      |

ğŸ§  **Concept:**
All these related components are **automatically grouped** inside the **Resource Group** you chose (`IntroAzureRG`).

